        What is Amazon Renewed?

        Amazon Renewed is your trusted destination for products that are inspected, tested, and refurbished as necessary to be fully functional.

        Quality you can afford

        Amazon Renewed products offer an affordable option so you can save on the brands you love.

        Products you can trust

        All products have been professionally inspected, tested, cleaned, and refurbished as necessary by Amazon-qualified suppliers.

        Purchases with an impact

        Your Amazon Renewed purchase extends the lifetime of this product and reduces electronic waste.

        Trusted coverage

        Your purchase is eligible for Amazon Renewed coverage in conjunction with Amazon's Return Policy and the A-to-z Guarantee.

        What should I expect to receive with my Amazon Renewed purchase?

        All Amazon Renewed purchases will come with accessories equivalent to those that shipped in the box when new. These items may not be original but will be compatible and fully functional. Amazon Renewed products will be packaged in either original packaging or in a new and clean cardboard box.

        In what condition can I expect my Amazon Renewed product to be?

        Product will be restored to its original factory settings and will be in one of the following cosmetic conditions Premium, Excellent, Good or Acceptable. Learn more

        Product Description

        This pre-owned or refurbished product has been professionally inspected and tested to work and look like new. How a product becomes part of Amazon Renewed, your destination for pre-owned, refurbished products: A customer buys a new product and returns it or trades it in for a newer or different model. That product is inspected and tested to work and look like new by Amazon-qualified suppliers. Then, the product is sold as an Amazon Renewed product on Amazon. If not satisfied with the purchase, renewed products are eligible for replacement or refund under the Amazon Renewed Guarantee.

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Sony probably has the best noise canceling technology which can really help u relax and is a godsend for travel.         5.0 out of 5 stars Best entry-level wireless ANC headphones with great battery life!
        Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
        Color: SilverVerified Purchase
        I purchased the Sony WH-1000XM5 Wireless active noise-canceling headphones a few months ago and have been using it actively since then, and I must say, they have completely blown me away! From the moment I put them on, I was transported into a world of uninterrupted audio and unmatched comfort. These headphones are an absolute game-changer, and here's why:

        Price: Although they may cost a few hundred bucks, they provide top of the line wireless ANC quality without spending thousands.

        Design: Minimalistic yet intriguing design. I got the silver version which makes it pop out against my hair. My girlfriend absolutely loves the look of the headphone and will even wear it as if it's an accessory.

        Sound: I personally was expecting better quality but nevertheless the audio was still very good. The active noise cancellation really isolates you into your own bubble where you hear only what you are listening to.

        Comfort: Extremely comfortable since its over the ear. Soft yet firm ear muffs that cradles your ears.

        Battery: More than happy with the battery, I would go multiple days with 2-4 hours of use each day on a single charge. Sometimes I would even go over a week without needing to charge.

        Companion App: Nice companion app that has a ton of features. Took me a while to setup but once you configure and get used to the various settings, it will be worth it.

        Rolidnot
        5.0 out of 5 stars One of the top Bluetooth headphone sets available for the price
        Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2022
        Verified Purchase
        This “B” (renewed) version of the Sony 1000/5’s is probably one of the best values for a top quality Bluetooth headphone currently available.

        It’s a no-frills presentation with the Sony “B” when it arrives. Brown Amazon box, zippered headphone case in a plastic bag, 90 day warranty info, the plug-in cord (yes, you can plug these in AND use them as Bluetooth phones!) and the power cord - see the photo.

        For a really in-depth review of these phones, refer to John Darko’s review of them on Darko Audio on the web. John’s review covers all the finer points in great detail.

        John’s video was recorded on 10/11/22 and compares the Sony WH-5000XM5’s to Bowers and Wilkins Px7 s2’s which are also $399 - the same price as the new Sony model.

        My take on the Sonys -

        - they fit well and are comfortable for a few hours
        - they can be used as a corded phone by leaving the power off and just plugging them in
        - the fold flat but they don’t fold up like the version 1-4 did. That’s not a big deal for me, I travel with ear buds, not over ear phones.
        - the app has a LOT of flexibility for adjusting the sound and system.
        - the controls work well on the right ear cup. Volume up and down, play/pause, track back or advance to name a few.
        - audio evaluations are inherently subjective. I have a pair of Meze 99’s Classics that I use daily as well. The Sony have great bass, the Meze phones do as well. The mid-range on the Meze seems more refined but I’m using the Ifi Zen Can amp tuned for the Meze 99’s so it’s not really a fair comparison.
        - not a mark or any visible defect anywhere on the “B” version that I bought. They look and sound brand new.

        For rhe $130 off off list for the “B” versus new, I don’t think you can get a better sound quality and app flexibility from a closed, over ear cordless phone for the price. Hope that helps!

The mid-range on the Meze seems more refined but I’m using the Ifi Zen Can amp tuned for the Meze 99’s so it’s not really a fair comparison.
        - not a mark or any visible defect anywhere on the “B” version that I bought. They look and sound brand new.

        For rhe $130 off off list for the “B” versus new, I don’t think you can get a better sound quality and app flexibility from a closed, over ear cordless phone for the price. Hope that helps!

        I'll start off by saying I definitely recommend these headphones for people with ADHD.         The ear cups are very comfortable and the top cushioning is fine for short periods of time, but when using these headphones for several hours, the top of my head starts to hurt due to the weight of the headphones.

        My biggest complaint is that the headphones randomly go through bursts of disconnecting from my device. Every once in a while, I'll have to reconnect the headphones over and over for around 5 minutes as it refuses to stay connected and I'm not sure why. The rest of my bluetooth devices do not have this issue.

        Overall, I like the noise suppression and the sleek design of the headphones and I think it would definitely work for people who use the headphones for only a few hours at a time but if you are planning on using it for extended periods of time, it may not be for you if you have a sensitive head.
